description: The Nebulous Mirage has been ambushed in mid-warp by a deadly Olgom privateer, halting the last leg of Ronen and his mother's journey to their homeland. Refused aid by his Mesozora kinsmen, Ronen joins Captain Nielrich's crew in rushing to the strong point, only to be snatched en route by mysterious, steel-suited agents of a powerful, dark master. Even after the goddess Sahssa Rai intervenes on his behalf, Ronen and his allies must now stop an enemy battalion still aboard! The final battle has begun!

The invading Olgom battalion overwhelms most of the Nebulous Mirage's defenses! With the Goddess departed to fend off more Olgom cruisers, it is now up to Ronen, the Manowar warrior girls, and Nielrich's valiant crew to repel the rest of the lethal boarding party-especially their deadliest member, the being known as the Vorrak. Impervious to conventional weapons, it can destroy them all! Will Ronen survive to reuinite with his mother?
Translates Emerald Warriors #13, Green Lantern Corps #61-63 & War of the Green Lanterns Aftermath #1-2.

The T.I.A. will renew its bacteriological weapons and will tune Arms with bug. These weapons are an invention of Professor Bacterio-based bacteria, which are inoculated to an animal. These animals have different properties that become a dangerous weapon. Mort and Phil will have to test the performance of these weapons-bug.

The wife of the CEO wants to organize a soiree to commemorate the 25 anniversary of the laying of the foundation stone of the TIA Mort and Phil will organize everything to make the party a success.

This cartoon is one of the last of the "black stage" of Ibanez. The first eight pages have signature Ibanez-buffer, but the remaining episodes, which seem to be made by someone else, do not bother to put it. The editor Julia Galan questioned the Ibanez deliver such poor quality material, both graphic and plot like this cartoon (and espantajomanes and The Inspector General), which would later renewal of the series.
name: El gran sarao

description:
After 664* issues and 14 years, this is the last issue of Battle.

Mostly reprint, Battle is a shadow of its former self and this final issue almost seems like an afterthought with only an 'exciting news in this issue' banner on the front cover to mark its passing. Shame.

Charley's War, Storm Force and Johnny Red all continue in Eagle issue 306.
